A fire left two shacks destroyed at Heinz Park in Phillipi on Thursday. It is believed that the fire started at around 6am on Thursday morning. According to Fire and rescue services spokesperson Theo Lane at this stage the cause of the fire is unknown. &#8220;There are no injuries or damages on the property&#8221;, said Lane. Police are currently not investigating this case however the fire and rescue team has vehicles on the scene. Meanwhile fire-fighters were deployed to Devil s Peak in Cape Town to put an end to a fire which lead to the incoming lane of De Waal Drive being closed.-TNA Reporter